    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beds, particularly those created in Europe prior to the 16th century, of various designs having a high wooden frame suspended over the head half of the bed, from which curtains may be hung in a tent-like fashion. Sparver beds typically do not have bedposts, but the frame may be attached to the wall or ceiling.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
